teammates to maintain and continually improve our existing and build new security tools and using modern software engineering practices What You Bring to the Compound Engineering Team: 6+ years of professional engineering experience in, Security, DevOps, SRE, InfoSec, Infrastructure, etc. Ability and experience learning new programming languages Exceptional judgment, strategic thinking and creative problem-solving skills with a strong analytical mindset Proficiency in taking threat models and applying effective network security strategies at scale BS or BA degree in Computer Science or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience Experience with these Technologies is \u201cNice to Have:\u201d Kubernetes and Google Cloud Platform experience Network Planning, IPS/IDS experience Formal analysis and code or model verification Benefits + Perks: Full medical, dental, and vision insurance???????????? Stock Options as an early employee of Compound Commuter benefits???????????? 3+ weeks of vacation Fitness reimbursement Paid parental leave???????????? Bike friendly office Open floor plan???????????? Regular team meals and outings A never-ending supply of office snacks + hot sauce We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We welcome qualified candidates of all races, creeds, genders, age, veteran status and sexuality to apply. Compound is an open-source, autonomous protocol built for developers, to unlock a universe of new financial applications. We are building a transparent money market for cryptocurrencies, while helping an ecosystem of applications built on top of Compound to grow, making it easier to access these financial markets. We are one of the most visible pioneers of decentralized finance - by joining us, you will truly have a hand in shaping the future of finance. Founded in 2017, Compound is backed by leading investors like Andreesen Horowitz, Bain Capital, Paradigm, Polychain Capital and Coinbase Ventures.????????